<DocLayout title="Policy & Research" description="AEGIS published papers, NIST submissions, policy responses, and research.">
  <h1>Policy &amp; Research</h1>

  <p>
    The AEGIS Initiative engages with policymakers, standards bodies, and the
    research community to advance governance-first approaches to AI safety. This
    section collects published papers, formal submissions, and policy responses.
  </p>

  <hr />

  <section>
    <h2>NIST Submissions</h2>
    <p>
      AEGIS has submitted formal public comments and position papers to the
      National Institute of Standards and Technology (NIST) as part of ongoing
      AI safety and governance rulemaking processes.
    </p>
    <p class="placeholder">Formal submissions will be published here with permanent URLs and DOI links as they become available.</p>
  </section>

  <hr />

  <section>
    <h2>Published Papers</h2>
    <p class="placeholder">
      Peer-reviewed and preprint publications will be listed here with DOI and
      Zenodo links. IEEE submissions will be noted when published.
    </p>
  </section>

  <hr />

  <section>
    <h2>Policy Responses</h2>
    <p>
      AEGIS responds to emerging policy proposals and regulatory frameworks that
      affect AI governance, safety, and security.
    </p>
    <p class="placeholder">
      Responses to White House AI frameworks, congressional proposals, and
      international regulatory developments will be published here as they are
      finalized.
    </p>
  </section>

  <hr />

  <section>
    <h2>Congressional Engagement</h2>
    <p class="placeholder">
      Open letters and formal communications with members of Congress will be
      published here with full text and response tracking.
    </p>
  </section>
</DocLayout>

